data.enText: to try to reach an agreement by formal discussion

data.chText: 政府不会和恐怖分子谈判。
data.enText: The government will not negotiate with terrorists.

data.chText: 我们一直在为增加工资进行协商。
data.enText: We have been negotiating for more pay.
to arrange or agree sth by formal discussion

data.chText: 达成交易；确立合同；商定条约内容 / 解决措施
我们成功地达成了释放人质的协议。
data.enText: We successfully negotiated the release of the hostages.
to successfully get over or past a difficult part on a path or route

data.chText: 攀登者必须攀越陡峭的岩壁。
data.enText: The climbers had to negotiate a steep rock face.

ex.chText: 她为了那些新化妆品和他讨价还价。
ex.enText: She bargained with him for the new cosmetics.

ex.chText: 工人们谈判再一次提高工资的条件。
ex.enText: The workers bargained a new wage increase.

ex.chText: 他们提出改善工作环境的要求。
ex.enText: They bargained for an improved working environment.

ex.chText: 如果你愿意谈判，你很有可能得到更好的待遇。
ex.enText: You are likely to get a better deal if you are prepared to bargain.

ex.chText: 为了争取更高的薪酬，工会几乎每年都要与资方进行谈判。
ex.enText: Unions bargain with employers for better rates of pay almost every year.

synonyms.bx: 主要用于商贸领域，指买卖双方为了达成协议而在价格等方面进行商谈。

d: 讨价还价，谈判，商谈条件

ex.chText: 双方正在为签订一份新合约进行谈判。
ex.enText: The two sides are negotiating for a new contract.

ex.chText: 通过与老板协商，他的薪水得以增加6%。
ex.enText: He has managed to negotiate a 6% pay increase with the boss.

ex.chText: 那两个国家商定了和平条约。
ex.enText: The two countries negotiated a peace treaty.
He is commissioned to negotiate with them.

ex.chText: 政府拒绝与叛乱分子谈判。
ex.enText: The government refused to negotiate with the rebels.

synonyms.bx: 较正式用词，尤指在商业、政治方面进行谈判或磋商。

tr: discuss the terms of an arrangement
example: They negotiated the sale of the house

tr: succeed in passing through, around, or over
example: The hiker negociated the high mountain pass

value.def: If people negotiate with each other or negotiate an agreement, they talk about a problem or a situation such as a business arrangement in order to solve the problem or complete the arrangement.

example.ex: It is not clear whether the president is willing to negotiate with the democrats...
example.tran: 还不清楚总统是否愿意和民主人士洽谈。

example.ex: When you have two adversaries negotiating, you need to be on neutral territory...
example.tran: 让敌对双方坐下来谈判时，你得保持中立。

example.ex: The local government and the army negotiated a truce...
example.tran: 地方政府和部队经过谈判达成休战协定。

example.ex: Western governments have this week urged him to negotiate and avoid force...
example.tran: 西方各国政府本周敦促他进行谈判，避免使用武力。

example.ex: The South African president has negotiated an end to white-minority rule...
example.tran: 南非总统已通过谈判达成协议，结束了少数白人的统治。

example.ex: His publishing house had just begun negotiating for her next books...
example.tran: 他的出版社刚刚开始就她随后几本书的出版问题进行商谈。

example.ex: There were reports that three companies were negotiating to market the drug.
example.tran: 有报道说，有3家公司在洽谈这种药的市场推广。

value.def: If you negotiate an area of land, a place, or an obstacle, you successfully travel across it or around it.

example.ex: Frank Mariano negotiates the desert terrain in his battered pickup...
example.tran: 弗兰克·马里亚诺驾驶他那辆破烂不堪的皮卡车成功穿越了沙漠地带。

example.ex: I negotiated the corner on my motorbike and pulled to a stop...
example.tran: 我骑摩托车顺利通过拐角，然后停了下来。

example.ex: I negotiated my way out of the airport and joined the flow of cars.
example.tran: 我驱车驶出机场，汇入车流之中。
